      "body" : "@K_7: Say for example that there are 10,000 distinct double value between 0.0 and 1.0 (in reality there are probably more). But if the range between <code>rangeMin</code>and <code>rangeMax</code> is large, then there might be 10,000,000 distinct double values between them. The result of <code>(rangeMax - rangeMin) * r.nextDouble()</code> will only choose between 10,000 of those possible 10,000,000 values. (I feel that this is not a perfect explanation, but maybe it helps a little bit...)"
