    "creation_date" : 1284067187,
    "answer_id" : 3680666,
    "question_id" : 3680637,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Use this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>double start = 400;\ndouble end = 402;\ndouble random = new Random().nextDouble();\ndouble result = start + (random * (end - start));\nSystem.out.println(result);\n</code></pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p><strong>EDIT:</strong></p>\n\n<p><code>new Random().nextDouble()</code>: randomly generates a number between 0 and 1.</p>\n\n<p><code>start</code>: start number, to shift number \"to the right\"</p>\n\n<p><code>end - start</code>: interval. Random gives you from 0% to 100% of this number, because random gives you a number from 0 to 1.</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p><strong>EDIT 2:</strong>\nTks @daniel and @aaa bbb. My first answer was wrong.</p>\n"
